China has announced a 14 per cent increase in the number of citizens living with HIV and AIDS.
There are more than 820,000 people affected in the country, according to health workers.
Only the second quarter of 2018 reported 40,000 new cases.
The vast majority of new cases are sexually transmitted, unlike in the past.
