Homosexuality was decriminalized in China in 1997, but the discrimination of the LGBT collective is common.
Considering the conservative values of the country, studies estimate that between 70 and 90 percent of men who have homosexual intercourse will end up marrying a woman.
Many of the transmissions of diseases are due to lack of adequate precautions for sexual intercourse.
